dc_title_s: Landmarks, San Mateo County Sea Level Rise Vulnerability Assessment Project Area, 2015
dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile represents landmarks in San Mateo County, California. Landmarks include: airports, beaches, cemeteries, public buildings, fire stations, golf courses, jails, historic sites, libraries, museums, parks, and schools. This layer is part of the San Mateo County Sea Level Rise Vulnerability Assessment Project. These data are intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production.
